Interface ProtectedIterator<Payload>

  • Type Parameters:

    All Superinterfaces:

    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractIndexedIterator, AbstractProtectedBidirectionalIterator, AbstractProtectedIterator, ArrayIterator, BooleanArrayIterator, ByteArrayIterator, CharacterArrayIterator, CountDownIterator, CountUpIterator, DoubleArrayIterator, EmptyIterator, EnumerationIterator, FloatArrayIterator, InfiniteIterator, IntegerArrayIterator, LongArrayIterator, LookAheadIterator, NodeListIterator, ObjectIterator, OptionalIterator, PairIterator, ProtectingBidirectionalIterator, ProtectingIterator, ShortArrayIterator, StringTokenizerIterator, TripleIterator, TupleIterator

    public interface ProtectedIterator<Payload>
extends Iterator<Payload>
    A ProtectedIterator is an Iterator that guarantees that every call to remove() throws an UnsupportedOperationException and doesn't alter the underlying data structure.

    ProtectedIterator is a marker interface.

    Since:
    1.2.0
    Author:
    Torsten Krause (tk at markenwerk dot net)
